00:12:20,412 --> 00:12:22,613
knew from our telemetry on Burnout Paradise.

203
00:12:25,015 --> 00:12:26,256
A really great part of being.

204
00:12:27,297 --> 00:12:30,018
part of EA is that we have access to all this great data

205
00:12:30,038 --> 00:12:32,259
across EA's portfolio.

206
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:35,861
And so what we saw here, this is looking at the average peak

207
00:12:35,901 --> 00:12:40,124
simultaneous users, weekly peak simultaneous users, back from

208
00:12:40,664 --> 00:12:43,906
2010 across a representative set of EA titles.

209
00:12:45,026 --> 00:12:47,147
And we were seeing that more and more players were now

210
00:12:47,187 --> 00:12:50,409
connecting to our servers, but then only a smaller proportion

211
00:12:50,429 --> 00:12:52,410
of those people were playing in online multiplayer.

212
00:12:54,912 --> 00:12:56,673
So while we were having more players connected.

213
00:12:57,834 --> 00:13:01,477
There aren't as many people as we wanted getting in to have that connected experience to have

214
00:13:01,517 --> 00:13:04,559
fun with their friends because they're just not going into online multiplayer.

215
00:13:05,039 --> 00:13:09,122
And I know from my own personal experience, online multiplayer, it's not always the most

216
00:13:09,162 --> 00:13:12,885
welcoming thing, especially as you start getting older, your reactions are slowing down, and

217
00:13:13,325 --> 00:13:15,167
there's only so many times I can get schooled by 17-year-olds.

218
00:13:15,187 --> 00:13:15,547
So then...

