00:26:12,691 --> 00:26:17,133
But it got really, really heavy use in our PC communities,

462
00:26:17,193 --> 00:26:20,434
especially in the hardcore PC community in Scandinavia

463
00:26:20,474 --> 00:26:21,774
and Eastern Europe and in Russia.

464
00:26:22,134 --> 00:26:25,395
Because PC players, that was their main tool

465
00:26:25,415 --> 00:26:26,195
for friend discovery.

466
00:26:27,455 --> 00:26:29,837
So they're able to go there because on the wall you could

467
00:26:29,897 --> 00:26:32,840
see posts from your friends of friends and replies from your

468
00:26:32,880 --> 00:26:33,440
friends of friends.

469
00:26:33,900 --> 00:26:37,483
So we had these huge, huge wall posts of people just

470
00:26:37,563 --> 00:26:39,725
introducing themselves to one another and getting acquainted

471
00:26:41,246 --> 00:26:43,668
to all share in that Autolog experience.

472
00:26:46,591 --> 00:26:48,832
The other thing we built that was in our front end was friend

473
00:26:48,852 --> 00:26:49,493
recommendations.

474
00:26:51,857 --> 00:26:55,580
As I said earlier, more than half of all players had only one or naught friends.

475
00:26:56,200 --> 00:26:58,142
And this was a game about playing with your friends.

476
00:26:58,242 --> 00:27:01,064
So if you've got no friends, now you can get friends.

